<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Mana Cost: 400<br>
Spell Duration: Instant<br>
Casting Time: 1.75 seconds<br>
Spell Recovery: 3.50 seconds<br>
Recast Delay: 2.25 seconds<br>
<br>
<br>
I don't know much about raids like you are all talking about but it seems to me you're not going to avoid getting summoned. I thinks you need 3 cleric targeted on the summoning point and ready to cast the above spell on whoever the unlucky person is. This business of MT holding all the agro may be over....   <br>
<br>
The advantage of this is that all the casters let loose from the very start and just do as much damage as they possibly can. You would be very surpised how fast PoP mobs fall (high attack but low HP) with wizards just pumping draughts into them as fast as they can. Also if you have a lot of wizards the mobs hate list starts bouncing all over they will summon, hit the victim a few times (whoever gets summoned need to just stop casting at that point) but then someone else goes to top of hate list really fast (cause all casters is pumping at full), and they forget about the first summon and summon in the new guy and start on him, but the old guy can still live.<br>
<br>
Anyway the &quot;DeathWalker Draught Pump Strategy&quot; is going to become more common with these agro changes. If you are going to be summoned at any point in the battle then there is no logic in holding back at all, you should flat out nuke max untill oom. This only applies to the PoP mobs, old world mobs with 100K plus hit points is another matter.<br>
<br>
Another thing is that when you are in exp groups you should try and group only with casters and not mellee. No matter what everyone thinks wizards undoubtably have the highest burst DPS of any class, and in PoP burst DPS is what wins, not long term substained DPS. Just get enough healers (and one slower at least - chanter is good cuause they can pull with their 1500HP rune) to heal you when you are summoned and no one should die. You should have 3300 or so HP with middleish gear and virtue - and some rune. You can be healed 1500 every 5 seconds with one cleric, and 1500 every 2.5 seconds with 2 clerics. And don't forget if all chasters is nuking with the same nuke the mob will be off you in about 5 seconds after you stop casting and summon or attack another.   <br>
