<br>
The ideas about melee aggro decay may be worth checking, but there's absolutely something more to the change that was implemented than the extension of the hatelist (the statement that over 60 people, the mobs didn't have room for you and 'forgot'). Wizards are never going to be 61st on a hate list unless they're afk, and I find it rather hard to believe that archers would be either (if their arrows were generating aggro). Since the intent of the past-60-hate-list-extension was to begin the Pain and Suffering for archers nerf/balance, it's obvious they ALSO did something directly to the amount of aggro ranged attacks do (which seems to have spilled over into spells). I don't have a good reason why some just aren't seeing any change. it could be some aspect or combination of gear, AA, spells used, mobs fought. Honestly, anyone who says &quot;pshaw, I'm not seeing it, screw you it's not there&quot; is blinding themselves. The game is COMPLEX. If  a lot of people empirically see a change in behavior you don't, it can come down to the fine detail level why you didn't.<br>
